FBIS4-43388 "drweu116_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Occhetto Seen as Contender for EP Presidency Occhetto Seen as Contender for EP Presidency BR1506143694 Rome LA REPUBBLICA in Italian 15 Jun 94 p 5 BR1506143694 Rome LA REPUBBLICA Italian BFN [Unattributed report: "Will Achille Become President in Strasbourg?"] [Text] Brussels -- Will [outgoing Democratic Party of the Left, PDS, Secretary] Achille Occhetto become president of the European Parliament [EP]? In the presidential contest which has just started in Strasbourg, the PDS' outgoing secretary's name is among six leading candidates, together with the two Belgian former Prime Ministers Leo Tindemans and Wilfried Martens (who are considered the favorites), Social Democrat John Hume from Northern Ireland, French center-right leader Dominique Baudis, and Spanish millionaire Abel Matutes. The election of the president will take place on 19 July. Occhetto's candidacy was suggested by a number of left-wing exponents, as the standard-bearer of the European Left against "neofascism" and "the victory of the Right in Italy."
